<L>__{exterior street early evening}
<A>__{she passes a grocery store, where a clock reads 6:15, and continues past other houses on the pleasant, green street. we hear parents telling their kids to come in for dinner, radios playing music or radio dramas. peaceful, charming. christine smiles, turns the corner, looks to her house and it's dark, closed up. no lights on inside, no music or dramas on the radio. dead silent. christine pauses, then picks up her pace. no need to panic, he could be upstairs asleep, could be in the back of the house, where the lights wouldn't show. she goes to the front door. it's unlocked. she enters }
